The paper discusses a framework for data sharing that involves blockchain and smart contracts, which are commonly used in the areas of computer security (cs.CR), databases (cs.DB), distributed computing (cs.DC), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SE). The focus on data ownership and control also suggests a connection to privacy and security concerns, which are often addressed in the cs.CR and cs.CY sub-categories.
